io.mosip.registration.service.sync

Interface SyncStatusValidatorService

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    SyncStatusValidatorServiceImpl

    public interface SyncStatusValidatorService
    It does the pre check before doing registration to ensure that the application can capture the Registration detail from individual. If the pre check fails, then don't allow the application to capture the detail from individual. Post completion of the respective sync process only the application can be used for Registration process. This would be called prior to New/ Update/ Lost UIN process.
    Author:
    Mahesh Kumar

    • Method Detail

      • validateSyncStatus

        ResponseDTO validateSyncStatus()
        It does the following validation:
        • No. of Offline packet count shouldn't be greater than what is provided in the config.
        • No. of days offline shouldn't be greater than what is provided in the config.
        • GPS related - center to machine distance shouldn't be greater than what is provided in the config.
        • No. of days, the application can run by skipping the Software update if available.
        Returns:
        Success or failure Error object along with the message.

      • isToBeForceUpdate

        boolean isToBeForceUpdate()
        This method helps to check whether application should perform force software update or not. It checks the software update flag value in the database table. If 'Y' then validate the days skipped for update. If the days are greater than the configured one at the properties then this method would return true otherwise false. This method would be invoked, during start up of the application.
        Returns:
        true for Force Update.
